    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.28a"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><unclear>0</unclear>2 Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">28a</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF DELAWARE
                        <lb/>
                    NEWARK, DELAWARE
                        <lb/>
                
                    DEPARTMENT OF ENGLISH</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>7 September 1954</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I understand that it is quite legitimate for fellow chancellors to submit names to each other for the Academy award. If you have no one especially cherished in mind, will you join me in putting up the name of Oliver St. John Gogarty &#8212; last of the great Celts, <add>(but an American <unclear>citizen</unclear>)</add> fine poet, whose <hi rend="underline">Collected Poems</hi> came out this year, 75 yrs. old, and in need of the Award?</p>
                <closer>      
                    <salute>With homage and warm regards,</salute>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Robert Hillyer</signed>
                    
                    John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt Esq
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
